  ["John 19:24, 28-29","The tunic and the hyssop","The tunic decided by lot fulfils Psalm 22:18; the vinegar, Psalm 69:21. And the sponge is fixed on a branch of hyssop — the plant used to apply the lamb's blood to the doorposts (Exodus 12:22).","The humblest detail carries the Passover."],
  ["John 19:33-37","The bones and the side","They break the legs of the other two; not his: “A bone of him will not be broken” (Exodus 12:46). The pierced side fulfils Zechariah 12:10: “They will look on him whom they pierced.”","The rule of the Passover lamb, to the letter."]],
  h2:"“It is finished”",
